Package: meteoHazard
Title: Meteorological Hazard Predictions for Waste Management
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("R. Shannon", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "burrows_51mustard@icloud.com")
Description: Turns meteorological data into management-relevant predictions and
    warnings for waste-management operations. Provides the Thermal Work Limit
    (TWL), the maximum sustainable metabolic rate (W/m²) for workers in
    thermally stressful environments, based on the methodology of Brake & Bates
    (2002) <doi:10.1080/104732202317070947>, alongside (planned) odour-dispersion
    and wind-blown-litter predictors. Part of the 'tidyWaste' family of packages.
URL: https://github.com/vorpalvorpal/meteoHazard
BugReports: https://github.com/vorpalvorpal/meteoHazard/issues
